FAILURES: 0
NOTES (non-blocking): 4
  - whitespace-only area silently falls back to NATIONWIDE sweep (documented as empty==None; an LLM passing '  ' would re-spill — improbable input, fail-open edge)
  - cache key = sha256(source||params||hour-vintage)[:32]; no session_id in the key — cross-session sharing of identical queries is BY DESIGN (FR-DC-3) and cannot leak: artifact content is purely param-determined
  - alias-ordering collision: {state:'Florida', area:'TX'} -> {'area': 'Florida'} (first-key wins, not canonical-wins; both values still STATE-SCOPED so no nationwide spill — mislabeled state at worst)
  - residual leak path: {area_code:'TX'} -> {'area_code': 'TX'}; 'area_code'/'us_state' are not aliased and **_extra_ignored absorbs them silently -> unscoped CONUS sweep. Mitigated by the declaration (Gemini sees 'area') but not closed.
